reviews_data.review_text: Overall I am very impressed with this location. Coffee is great, service is really good, and the croissants are amazing.
Great coffee! Love the blueberry cold foam!

Cute busy little coffee shop. I ordered an iced caramel latte because they create their own syrups. Unfortunately, the drink wasn't good. The caramel tastes store bought and the coffee is sub par. May come back to try a pastry, but won't be returning for coffee.
1st time here and will definitely come back. Everyone was so nice and helpful.  Iced coffee was amazing!!

reviews_data.review_text:
An excellent latte, perhaps a bit spendy but this is one of the more exclusive neighborhoods in Charlotte. Parking is a challenge as the street spots are limited to handicapped. You'll need to find a visitor spot in the parking deck.

Inside and outside seating. It's laid out quite nicely with comfortable seating for working with a laptop while enjoying your coffee. Bright and modern vibe here.

We stopped in for a latte and shared it, sitting and watching the customer flow for a bit. Next time, I might bring the laptop and hang out properly.

reviews_data.review_text: Only 3 stars because the croissant was hard as a rock. The drip coffee wasn't to my liking, but I'm no coffee expert so  take that as you wish. The location is good, the team was busy and cordial. I went for the coffee so since it's not to my liking I'll try other places in the area.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for your feedback. I'm sorry the croissant and coffee didn't hit the mark. We're glad our team made a good impression, and we'd love another chance to get it right. If you'd like to share more, feel free to reach out at southpark@summitcoffee.com.

reviews_data.review_text: Bring a sweater, it’s freezing inside! Chai latte is excellent.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are glad you liked the chai Haley. We’ll be sure to  keep an eye on that thermostat. Thanks for the review!

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee was TERRIBLE one of the worst I’ve had— I got the drip coffee. Pastries looked bad, Tous de Jours is right around the corner and better by miles. The decor was pretty bland just not very inviting, the staff was nice enough though.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. We’re really sorry to hear that your visit didn’t meet expectations, especially when it comes to the drip coffee and overall experience. We take that seriously, and we’re genuinely disappointed to hear that we missed the mark for you. Our team takes great pride in creating a welcoming environment and serving quality coffee and pastries, so this review is tough to read- but we appreciate the honesty and the opportunity to improve. We’ll be sharing your feedback with our team to make sure we are addressing any quality inconsistencies and continue to raise the bar. Thank you again for stopping in, and for acknowledging the kindness of our staff- we hope we can welcome you back in the future and provide the kind of experience we are known for.

Another coffee shop, coffee was good and tables available. Nothing outstanding and everything was ok
Summit coffee is always a good idea.
One of the best coffee shops I’ve ever been to. Amazing customer service. If I could give this 6 stars I would.

OK coffee shop. Went in the late afternoon everything was ok
Good coffee and nice atmosphere.

Espresso was delicious!
Bagels and muffins!
Great french press for hot teas!
Hot Chocolate....
Coffee, all styles.
the most delicious coffee in town.. the food is not tasty at all

Great coffee, nice place with friendly service. Acoustics are good. I got a coffee and a chocolate croissant with lots of chocolate heated up. Yum. Recommend this place for hanging out or doing computer work.

Vibe inside was off, I guess that comes with the territory of going to this location during working hours. Service was ok. I had no idea the cold foam was pre made and came out of a container or I would not have paid extra to have that on my coffee...
Great taste and the girls were very sweet
Smoothest oat milk latte, loveliest seating, sweetest service…my favorite place to work away from home. Thank you Summit staff!
The best matcha in town!! Add blueberry syrup during the summer months- it’s delish!!
The best matcha in town!! Add blueberry syrup during the summer months- it’s delish!!

My husband had a mocha latte and I had the matcha latte. Quick service and delicious drinks. I would come back to this location if I lived in Charlotte. They did have overnight oats I would have tried if we were going to breakfast after stopping here.

Would recommend.
My coffee was super yummy. There was only one person working there with a pretty big crowd, so it took a little while, but the coffee was worth the wait.
I got an iced latte with raspberry syrup and it was ok, coffee was a little bitter and needed more milk so I asked to get some and it tasted a bit better.
Great place to get work done! Staff is friendly  & helpful.
Love this place! They have the best homemade chocolate chip cookies and yummy matcha
Excellent coffee. Properly hit the spot after a lengthy multi city overnight trip.
We just got coffee and it was great - first refill in drip coffee was free! Great place to sit outside and enjoy nice weather and conversation over quality coffee.
Great little spot to meet for coffee- excellent baristas very friendly… just so crowded and a little loud but after it cleared out a bit it was great
We had a latte and a drip. Both were excellent. The ham and cheese croissant was very good. The quiche was good but kind of boring and "wet". Service was great.

Super cute coffee shop. The kids loved the hot chocolates and my wife really enjoyed the matcha tea latte. My chai was solid, hindsight being 20/20 I should have asked for some vanilla. Bathroom was super clean and plenty of outdoor seating available!
The café is excellent! They serve top-quality coffee and delicious cookies. I appreciate that they use real dishes instead of plastic cups, adding to the overall experience.
Love this place! Customer service and coffee always good. Just wish it was a little faster but that won’t stop me from going for my java

reviews_data.review_text: Seating is tight. It was hard to find a place to plug in my computer. My beverage was hot and the staff friendly.
Great customer service! Best cappuccino we have had by far. Clean and cozy atmosphere.

Great experience, lovely atmosphere, and good coffee. Quintin was incredibly friendly and helpful - she took the time to make recommendations for a first time visit and helped me find a gluten free option on the menu. Highly recommend!

Sumit Coffee is a delightful oasis for coffee enthusiasts, offering a perfect blend of friendly, fast service and a cozy atmosphere. The skilled baristas not only deliver your order promptly but also do so with a warm and welcoming demeanor that enhances the overall experience.

The cappuccino at Sumit Coffee is a true work of art, boasting a rich and velvety texture that exemplifies the expertise behind the counter. The Macha, too, is a treat for those seeking a taste of the exotic, with a balance that reflects careful preparation and quality ingredients.

Situated in a charming shopping area, Sumit Coffee provides not only a caffeine fix but also a scenic backdrop for your coffee indulgence. The ambiance is complemented by the surroundings, creating a space that invites you to linger and enjoy your favorite brew.

Whether you're a devoted coffee connoisseur or simply in need of a quick pick-me-up, Sumit Coffee delivers on both fronts. The combination of excellent service, top-notch beverages, and a prime location makes it a go-to destination for those seeking a coffee experience that goes beyond the ordinary. Sumit Coffee stands as a testament to the idea that a great cup of coffee is not just a drink but a moment to be savored.
I didn’t realize they were in the complex. Excellent coffee and great service
Great coffee shop. Summit descent is a wonderful roast. Coffee is excellent. Service is ok. Parking can be difficult.

I'm not sure what kind of customers they are used to, but a man who could be the manager or the owner treated me and my husband rudely. This man came to our table to ask if we intended to order something, my husband had just placed an order for two coffees but had gone to the car to get his cell phone which he had forgotten. Detail the coffe came cold. We don’t intend to go back.
Had a cappuccino here that was okay, but the espresso had a bit of an unpleasant aftertaste. Not a big fan of their blend here.
Super cute tucked away spot

This place is a gem! Delicious coffee. We had iced oat americano and cherry 🍒 coke float— my husband loved it!! The atmosphere is so cozy! Definitely coming back!!
Also, their bathroom cleanliness needs to be applauded. And hand soap smells so yumm! 🤍
This location is always a vibe with friendly staff and love seeing people working, meeting which goes to its atmosphere.
Solids coffee shop.
Favorite coffee spot. Tried the blueberry foam latte. Seasonal drinks and pastries.
Young and young at heart meet here for reliable espresso treats and a trendy scene.
Good strong cup of coffee. Raw sugar was impossible to get out.
Beautiful place, great atmosphere and delicious coffee. Also, tried their beans and they were really good.

I like working from this summit a lot because the view of piedmont towne center is really nice and the store itself it very clean and pretty on the inside. They have really good matcha and a gluten free morning muffin that’s delicious. Their overnight oats are super good as well. It’s very cold inside tho, I typically need a jacket even in the summer if I am going to be staying for most of the day.
Delicious coffee and the pimento cheese scone was amazing
My chai latte was excellent. Service was fast and friendly.
Great coffee and atmosphere, staff is always so friendly.
Nice coffee, espresso carefully prepared.
I unfortunately paid $7 for a latte but it’s a nice place to work, lots of light and good seating
Always great coffee & flavors, definitely recommend.
Great atmosphere but the latte had too much (oat) milk making the coffee taste weak. Or maybe the espresso is just on the weaker side as it is. Positive note, clean bathroom🫱🏾‍🫲🏽 & fun ideas
I got the mocha! Loved this little spot. Great place to grab coffee and talk!
Really cute place to grab a coffee. The food selections are limited but they have good coffee drinks and the ambiance is cute.
Me encanto
Great atmosphere and excellent cappuccino. I will definitely be back when I am in the area.
Everything you want a coffee shop to be! Delicious lattes, homemade syrups, friendly baristas, and great vibe. With indoor or outdoor seating, it’s the ideal place to meet friends or clients!
Super cute coffee shop.  Great place for work study
Delightful baristas and the chai and matcha are incredible!

To give this coffee shop its due is to invent new, better words for hospitality, service, and grace. My friend and I stopped in and experienced delicious (and strong) espresso, chai latte, as well as exemplary attention from the owner and staff. Summit Coffee South Park hit it out of the park and created an all round great feeling for the rest of my day.
The most beautiful coffee shop in Charlotte.
Best place ever to enjoy a cup!  Staff is so gracious and welcoming!  Brian & Scott
The coffee is very very strong. Too strong for my taste.
Quiet and clean inside and great location!
Love how they make homemade syrups and this seasonal drink was amazing. It’s a blueberry honeysuckle iced coffee topped with blue vanilla cold foam!
Great coffee shop! Love the decor and variety of drinks.
Americano on par 😌☕️
Great latte and chill ambience. Beautiful little terrace too

I was on my way to another coffee shop when I spotted Summit Coffee.  It's a charming, quiet shop, and the two men behind the counter were very pleasant.  I ordered the house coffee and a blueberry muffin and thoroughly enjoyed both.   I would highly recommend Summit Coffee and I'll definitely be back.
Nice new, clean, modern atmosphere. Friendly staff. Indoor/outdoor seating. Draft beer as well. They need more food/bakery options.
Made with a Latte care :)
Amazing coffee. Amazing stuff. Beautiful inside. All I was looking for!!!
This place is awesome! The coffee is great but I especially love the chai lattes!!! Wonderful atmosphere too
Wonderful customer service, excellent selection.  Delightful atmosphere.

I’ve been to their other locations- this one is my favorite. They sell wine and beer here as well! Brought my coffee to my table and gave excellent service. The interior is the most aesthetically pleasing place to take pictures with friends, do homework, work, or have an afternoon to yourself. (Will take pictures next time)
Soft cushions! Good internet. Does get chilly.
Love their coffee! Beautiful space too. Their croissants are from Copain and are delicious.
